00:05:54.850 --> 00:06:00.310
But that's exactly what so many
of us do on a regular basis.

00:06:00.310 --> 00:06:03.739
So my question is really,
what's going on here?

00:06:03.739 --> 00:06:06.280
And I think that the answer to
the question on the next slide

00:06:06.280 --> 00:06:07.613
gives us some insight into this.

00:06:07.613 --> 00:06:10.750
So answer this question,
does physical exercise

00:06:10.750 --> 00:06:12.245
improve physical health?

00:06:12.245 --> 00:06:13.870
For people in the
room, raise your hand

00:06:13.870 --> 00:06:15.640
if you think the answer is yes.

00:06:15.640 --> 00:06:16.471
OK.

00:06:16.471 --> 00:06:18.970
Let the record show that's every
single person in this room,

00:06:18.970 --> 00:06:19.469
right?

00:06:19.469 --> 00:06:22.090
And I'm getting some strange
looks like, why are you asking

00:06:22.090 --> 00:06:23.980
such a ridiculous question?

00:06:23.980 --> 00:06:25.780
And what I want
to suggest to you

00:06:25.780 --> 00:06:27.490
is the reason we get
on exercise bikes

00:06:27.490 --> 00:06:31.870
or we go for jogs is because we
have a cultural understanding

00:06:31.870 --> 00:06:35.410
that this is true, that we need
to exercise our bodies to be

00:06:35.410 --> 00:06:36.430
physically healthy.

00:06:36.430 --> 00:06:38.140
It's such a common
understanding that we

00:06:38.140 --> 00:06:40.120
think it's a ridiculous
question to ask.

00:06:40.120 --> 00:06:42.495
But what I want to suggest to
you-- and actually, argue--

00:06:42.495 --> 00:06:45.070
is that this understanding
didn't come out of thin air.

00:06:45.070 --> 00:06:49.330
It actually came through a
dedicated set of research

00:06:49.330 --> 00:06:51.880
questions and science
that pursued understanding

00:06:51.880 --> 00:06:54.250
the relationship with
regard to physical health

00:06:54.250 --> 00:06:55.250
and physical exercise.

00:06:55.250 --> 00:06:59.860
And one of the key, really,
pioneers in this area

00:06:59.860 --> 00:07:04.395
was actually an Air Force
captain, who wrote-- literally,

00:07:04.395 --> 00:07:05.770
wrote the book
called "Aerobics."

00:07:05.770 --> 00:07:07.840
He was one of the
first people who put,

00:07:07.840 --> 00:07:10.720
maybe 27,000 or so
military service members

00:07:10.720 --> 00:07:14.020
through lots of different tests
to come up with what we now

00:07:14.020 --> 00:07:15.330
consider everyday knowledge.

00:07:15.330 --> 00:07:17.440
This notion of
10,000 steps a day,

00:07:17.440 --> 00:07:20.170
or the fact that our
cardiovascular health depends

00:07:20.170 --> 00:07:22.030
on our ability to
engage in certain kinds

00:07:22.030 --> 00:07:24.560
of aerobic exercise
comes from his work.

00:07:24.560 --> 00:07:27.760
And of course, many, many other
research studies followed.

00:07:27.760 --> 00:07:30.640
And the way in which
this field of research

00:07:30.640 --> 00:07:33.100
has parsed the question
of physical health

00:07:33.100 --> 00:07:35.320
and physical exercise
is as follows, right?

00:07:35.320 --> 00:07:37.630
We know that we can
look at the physiology.

00:07:37.630 --> 00:07:39.610
We can actually
conduct research that

00:07:39.610 --> 00:07:42.970
has people exercising and look
at their oxygen consumption,

00:07:42.970 --> 00:07:46.900
or whatever it is.

00:07:46.900 --> 00:07:49.000
Carbon dioxide levels
in the blood, et cetera.

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:52.210
And that gives us an
indication of their health.

00:07:52.210 --> 00:07:54.857
So while they're actually
performing the act of exercise,

00:07:54.857 --> 00:07:55.690
we can look at them.

00:07:55.690 --> 00:07:57.065
We can look at
people that choose

00:07:57.065 --> 00:07:59.560
as a lifestyle to engage in
physical activity-- elite

00:07:59.560 --> 00:08:00.460
athletes.

00:08:00.460 --> 00:08:03.010
And we can see what their
physiology looks like at rest,

00:08:03.010 --> 00:08:05.200
to see if it differs from
those that don't actually

00:08:05.200 --> 00:08:06.950
exercise on a regular basis.

00:08:06.950 --> 00:08:09.550
And that there are differences
in the direction of health.

00:08:09.550 --> 00:08:13.420
We can look at structural
changes or protein expression.

00:08:13.420 --> 00:08:14.950
There are so many
different ways we

00:08:14.950 --> 00:08:18.490
can establish the
link between engaging

00:08:18.490 --> 00:08:20.680
in particular
activities and health.

00:08:20.680 --> 00:08:22.750
And, finally performance.

00:08:22.750 --> 00:08:25.747
We can look at how people
do when they actually

00:08:25.747 --> 00:08:27.580
engage in activity in
terms of how well they

00:08:27.580 --> 00:08:31.550
perform a challenge task, for
example, of running a marathon.

00:08:31.550 --> 00:08:34.240
So this type of research
has actually resulted in--

00:08:34.240 --> 00:08:36.549
and this is an
underestimation, probably,

00:08:36.549 --> 00:08:40.510
around 300,000 articles
since 1980 that

00:08:40.510 --> 00:08:41.740
have been done on this topic.

00:08:41.740 --> 00:08:44.470
And that volume of
research is what I would

00:08:44.470 --> 00:08:47.170
say is why we have the answer.

00:08:47.170 --> 00:08:48.070
So plainly, yes.

00:08:48.070 --> 00:08:50.260
That of course,
physical activity

00:08:50.260 --> 00:08:52.400
is tied to physical health.

00:08:52.400 --> 00:08:52.900
OK.

00:08:52.900 --> 00:08:53.830
So I want to make that point.

00:08:53.830 --> 00:08:56.200
It seems trivial, but it
didn't come out of nowhere.

00:08:56.200 --> 00:08:58.420
And that now because
of this research,

00:08:58.420 --> 00:09:01.210
we are at a point
in our culture--

00:09:01.210 --> 00:09:04.930
and actually, around the
world, that our public health

00:09:04.930 --> 00:09:08.500
officials can give us very
precise evidence-based guidance

00:09:08.500 --> 00:09:09.460
on what to do.

00:09:09.460 --> 00:09:10.960
It's not just that
it's good for us,

00:09:10.960 --> 00:09:13.360
but here's what you
should do to optimize.

00:09:13.360 --> 00:09:14.440
All right.

00:09:14.440 --> 00:09:16.270
So I think I've made that point.

00:09:16.270 --> 00:09:19.030
And I want to switch gears to
a different kind of a question.

00:09:19.030 --> 00:09:22.491
Does mental exercise improve
psychological well-being?

00:09:22.491 --> 00:09:23.740
How many people would say yes?

