00:51:01.650 --> 00:51:02.940
It was a fantastic talk.

00:51:02.940 --> 00:51:03.330
AMISHI JHA: Thank you.

00:51:03.330 --> 00:51:05.560
MARIO GALARRETA: We are going
to have time for a couple--

00:51:05.560 --> 00:51:06.370
three questions.

00:51:06.370 --> 00:51:10.444
So if anybody in the
room has a question.

00:51:10.444 --> 00:51:11.770
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:51:11.770 --> 00:51:16.240
You mentioned that public
knowledge and interest

00:51:16.240 --> 00:51:18.910
in mindfulness training
and mindfulness in general

00:51:18.910 --> 00:51:22.240
has become exponentially
more popular in recent years.

00:51:22.240 --> 00:51:25.120
I was wondering how the
pop culture understanding

00:51:25.120 --> 00:51:28.210
of mindfulness affects
the perception of the work

00:51:28.210 --> 00:51:29.216
that you do?

00:51:29.216 --> 00:51:31.090
AMISHI JHA: Well, it
leads me to giving talks

00:51:31.090 --> 00:51:33.250
like the one I
just gave, which is

00:51:33.250 --> 00:51:36.700
that I think that the
public interest is outpacing

00:51:36.700 --> 00:51:39.110
what the science can deliver.

00:51:39.110 --> 00:51:40.630
And I think that
part of it means

00:51:40.630 --> 00:51:42.910
that as scientists who are
actively doing this work,

00:51:42.910 --> 00:51:45.520
we have to say where
we're really at.

00:51:45.520 --> 00:51:47.410
Because it's not a cure-all.

00:51:47.410 --> 00:51:49.330
Its effects aren't
lasting if you just

00:51:49.330 --> 00:51:51.220
read a book on mindfulness.

00:51:51.220 --> 00:51:54.220
And that type of
notion can actually

00:51:54.220 --> 00:51:55.960
be problematic for people.

00:51:55.960 --> 00:51:58.150
And probably, would
result in them disengaging

00:51:58.150 --> 00:51:59.983
from practicing altogether
because they have

00:51:59.983 --> 00:52:01.510
an unrealistic view
of what it takes

00:52:01.510 --> 00:52:04.322
to actually see benefits and
change in their own life.

00:52:04.322 --> 00:52:05.280
So that's where I'm at.

00:52:05.280 --> 00:52:07.330
I'm at trying to course
correct a little bit

00:52:07.330 --> 00:52:09.989
and have the hype
kind of dwindle

00:52:09.989 --> 00:52:11.530
and the rigor of
the science increase

00:52:11.530 --> 00:52:14.492
to get it to a better place.

00:52:14.492 --> 00:52:15.390
MARIO GALARRETA: OK.

00:52:15.390 --> 00:52:16.570
