00:52:20.570 --> 00:52:22.390
AUDIENCE: Hi, thanks
for your talk.

00:52:22.390 --> 00:52:24.910
I had a question about
the emotional side.

00:52:24.910 --> 00:52:28.240
So have there been
research published

00:52:28.240 --> 00:52:32.770
on the effect of the emotions
while either being mindful

00:52:32.770 --> 00:52:35.980
or in the moment of stress,
like how has that been handled?

00:52:35.980 --> 00:52:40.150
Whether it's a flight or fight
or fear, anger, or anything

00:52:40.150 --> 00:52:40.792
like that.

00:52:40.792 --> 00:52:42.000
AMISHI JHA: Yeah, absolutely.

00:52:42.000 --> 00:52:45.670
So I think that that
is a very important--

00:52:45.670 --> 00:52:47.710
and it may seem
unrelated to attention,

00:52:47.710 --> 00:52:50.500
but it's actually
deeply intertwined

00:52:50.500 --> 00:52:53.590
with the attentional
work that I was sharing.

00:52:53.590 --> 00:52:56.680
Because it ends up
that these aspects

00:52:56.680 --> 00:53:01.990
of our emotional response to an
experience tend to be the thing

00:53:01.990 --> 00:53:05.230
that can hijack our attention
away from the moment.

00:53:05.230 --> 00:53:07.220
So if you're having
a fear response

00:53:07.220 --> 00:53:10.480
or you're having
anger, that content

00:53:10.480 --> 00:53:12.280
consumes the
attentional resources

00:53:12.280 --> 00:53:13.780
available in the moment.

00:53:13.780 --> 00:53:16.840
So part of what we're seeing
actually in some of our work

00:53:16.840 --> 00:53:19.180
is that when we increase
the capacity of working

00:53:19.180 --> 00:53:21.010
memory and attention,
we can actually

00:53:21.010 --> 00:53:23.180
improve emotion regulation.

00:53:23.180 --> 00:53:25.120
So for example, in
pre-deployment Marines,

00:53:25.120 --> 00:53:27.210
what we found is that
if we do nothing at all,

00:53:27.210 --> 00:53:28.450
their negative mood--

00:53:28.450 --> 00:53:30.910
as you can imagine,
their negative mood

00:53:30.910 --> 00:53:33.220
increased in the
eight-week period

00:53:33.220 --> 00:53:35.650
as they approached
pre-deployment.

00:53:35.650 --> 00:53:37.210
Got more negative.

00:53:37.210 --> 00:53:39.910
And stress, the same way.

00:53:39.910 --> 00:53:40.900
Anxiety, the same way.

00:53:40.900 --> 00:53:43.002
Everything gets more profound.

00:53:43.002 --> 00:53:44.710
But when we offered
mindfulness training,

00:53:44.710 --> 00:53:48.610
those that actually practiced
did not get that increase,

00:53:48.610 --> 00:53:51.400
but only if they actually showed
improvements in their working

00:53:51.400 --> 00:53:52.760
memory.

00:53:52.760 --> 00:53:55.390
So what we think is happening
is that that ability to hold

00:53:55.390 --> 00:53:57.880
and grow this
mental white space,

00:53:57.880 --> 00:54:00.392
this internal
capacity to control

00:54:00.392 --> 00:54:02.350
the contents of your
present moment experience,

00:54:02.350 --> 00:54:04.930
can give you a better
ability to handle

00:54:04.930 --> 00:54:07.300
and deal with those
negative emotions.

00:54:07.300 --> 00:54:08.611
Does that answer your question?

00:54:08.611 --> 00:54:09.111
OK.

00:54:13.177 --> 00:54:14.510
AUDIENCE: Just a quick question.

