00:54:54.210 --> 00:54:56.250
all those are fluid, right?

00:54:56.250 --> 00:54:58.150
I mean, nobody's
promising that you're

00:54:58.150 --> 00:55:00.570
going to have fully enlightened,
never disregulate person

00:55:00.570 --> 00:55:01.620
going through these programs.

00:55:01.620 --> 00:55:03.270
You're going to have people
that have better attention

00:55:03.270 --> 00:55:04.699
and better mood, for example.

00:55:04.699 --> 00:55:06.240
And what we've done
is we started out

00:55:06.240 --> 00:55:10.170
with using this 8-week model
of MBSR, which is around 8

00:55:10.170 --> 00:55:12.602
weeks and 40 hours or more.

00:55:12.602 --> 00:55:15.060
And what we did in our studies
with active-duty military is

00:55:15.060 --> 00:55:16.680
we said, we're going to
still hold this 8 week

00:55:16.680 --> 00:55:19.200
period of time, but we're
going to actually cut the time

00:55:19.200 --> 00:55:21.120
to 24 hours in 1 program.

00:55:21.120 --> 00:55:22.830
So that would be 3 hours a week.

00:55:22.830 --> 00:55:25.080
In another group, we'd
do 2 hours a week.

00:55:25.080 --> 00:55:26.160
So 16.

00:55:26.160 --> 00:55:29.130
In another group, we did
1 hour a week, 8 hours.

00:55:29.130 --> 00:55:31.290
And what we looked to see
is what the differences

00:55:31.290 --> 00:55:32.952
were in their mood,
in their attention,

00:55:32.952 --> 00:55:34.410
in their working
memory, et cetera.

00:55:34.410 --> 00:55:37.170
And what we found is that we
could go as low as 8 hours

00:55:37.170 --> 00:55:42.270
and still see benefits, but
only if those 8 hours actually

00:55:42.270 --> 00:55:45.390
included an emphasis
on practice.

00:55:45.390 --> 00:55:47.440
So we had a comparison
8-hour program

00:55:47.440 --> 00:55:49.440
where the same trainer
talked about mindfulness,

00:55:49.440 --> 00:55:51.720
but only really talked
about mindfulness,

00:55:51.720 --> 00:55:54.390
wasn't spending as much time in
class practicing mindfulness.

00:55:54.390 --> 00:55:56.400
That was the equivalent
of doing nothing at all.

00:55:56.400 --> 00:55:59.430
So as you shorten the
duration of the training,

00:55:59.430 --> 00:56:03.420
the proportion of time spent
actually practicing in class

00:56:03.420 --> 00:56:04.380
is key.

00:56:04.380 --> 00:56:06.360
So now through my work
with Scott Rogers,

00:56:06.360 --> 00:56:09.390
we've gone on to see if 4
weeks or 2 weeks with 8 hours

00:56:09.390 --> 00:56:10.412
is beneficial.

00:56:10.412 --> 00:56:12.120
And what we're finding
is that we can now

00:56:12.120 --> 00:56:14.620
see in 4 weeks and 8
hours, the benefit.

00:56:14.620 --> 00:56:17.650
But that's more than half
the class being practice.

00:56:17.650 --> 00:56:21.523
So that's the nature
of how it's looking.

00:56:21.523 --> 00:56:22.356
MARIO GALARRETA: OK.

00:56:22.356 --> 00:56:23.466
